      "name": "Sticky Note1"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Job Sources\n\nThis workflow collects job listings from multiple remote job platforms.\n\n### Sources used\n• WeWorkRemotely\n• Remotive\n• Jobicy\n\nThese platforms provide APIs or RSS feeds that allow automated job retrieval.\n\nUsing multiple sources increases the chances of finding relevant opportunities.",
        "height": 304,
        "width": 544,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -1696,
        240
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "id": "30bade8a-0a80-40ec-b8bd-e2f9c2eab20c",
      "name": "Sticky Note2"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🌐 Job Data Sources (HTTP Requests)\n\nThis section fetches job listings from multiple remote job platforms using HTTP requests.\n\n### Sources used\n• WeWorkRemotely – RSS feed for remote programming jobs  \n• Remotive – Public API providing structured remote job listings  \n• Jobicy – Remote job API with job details and metadata  \n\n### What happens here\nEach HTTP Request node retrieves raw job data from its respective platform.\n\nThe response format may vary:\n• XML (RSS feed)\n• JSON (API response)\n\nThese responses are then sent to processing nodes where the data is:\n• parsed\n• cleaned\n• converted into a standardized structure\n\n### Standardized job fields\nAll sources are normalized into the following format:\n• company  \n• role / job title  \n• location  \n• experience requirement  \n• apply link  \n• source platform  \n\nThis ensures that jobs from different platforms can be merged and processed together later in the workflow.",
        "height": 672,
        "width": 752,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -352,
        416
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "id": "dc88182b-6ec7-48df-9e23-f43263b48ea9",
      "name": "Sticky Note3"
    },
